    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1866-10-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1866-10-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="170" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d170">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Campbell</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 35.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1866-10-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 23, 1866</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your despatch of the 1st
                            instant, No. 48, in which you have given a detailed and interesting
                            account of the late visit to Stockholm of the United States squadron,
                            composed of the double turreted monitor Miantonomoh and steamship
                            Augusta, under command of Captain Alexander Murray. Your proceedings on
                            the occasion are entirely approved, and it is very gratifying to know
                            that the officers of the fleet were received with such marked attention
                            and courtesy by his Majesty and the authorities of Sweden.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James H. Campbell,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
